<div id="outline-container-org1e9d70c" class="outline-2">
<h2 id="org1e9d70c">Redis&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;<span class="tag"><span class="database">database</span>&#xa0;<span class="db">db</span>&#xa0;<span class="redis">redis</span></span></h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org1e9d70c">
<p>
Redis is a in memeory key-value dataabase. Since it is a nosql database it can do a number of things.
</p>

<p>
It is commonly used as a cache system or a task queue.
</p>


<p>
Redis stands for remote dictionary server.
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org0efaa3a" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org0efaa3a">Topics</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org0efaa3a">
<ul class="org-ul">
<li><a href="20230330161754-redis_expiration.html#ID-d7ec3a25-ea89-4ab5-ac11-dd4fd05f94a9">redis expiration</a></li>
<li></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org367c1ce" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org367c1ce">Storage and Retrieval</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org367c1ce">
<p>
Like other key value databases.
All keys are strings.
Data is Accessed by keys.
</p>

<p>
Keys exists in a "key" space (think database)
Single commands are atomic.
</p>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org96ae7bc" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org96ae7bc">Data Types</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org96ae7bc">
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgd310d16" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgd310d16">String</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-orgd310d16">
<p>
Normal sequence of bytes. They are binary safe, so they are not null terminated.
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org76e2186" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org76e2186">Hashes</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org76e2186">
<p>
Represents a collection of key val pairs
</p>

<p>
The command prefixes start with H
</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org1838624" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org1838624">Commands</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org1838624">
<p>
I will not list all the commands here, just the most used ones
</p>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org3418661" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org3418661">SET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org3418661">
<p>
Set is used to set a key to a value
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell"><span style="font-weight: bold;">set</span> name foo
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orge397e8e" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orge397e8e">GET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-orge397e8e">
<p>
Get is used to get a key's value
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">get name
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-org5e9bbf3" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org5e9bbf3">Del</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org5e9bbf3">
<p>
Del removes a key
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">del name
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div id="outline-container-org511b4d4" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="org511b4d4">GETSET</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-org511b4d4">
<p>
Get a key's value and set a new one
</p>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">getset name foo
</pre>
</div>
<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setset name foo1
</pre>
</div>
<p>
If you ran it one more time you would get foo1
</p>
</div>
</div>
<div id="outline-container-orgd343236" class="outline-4">
<h4 id="orgd343236">SETNX</h4>
<div class="outline-text-4" id="text-orgd343236">
<p>
Set a key if its non existent (is this a lock?)
</p>

<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setnx name bar
</pre>
</div>
<p>
#+RESULTS
</p>
<pre class="example">
(integer) 0
</pre>


<p>
See since name exists it failed to set the key
</p>


<div class="org-src-container">
<pre class="src src-shell">setnx name1 bar
</pre>
</div>
<p>
#+RESULTS
</p>
<pre class="example">
(integer) 1
</pre>
</div>
</div>
</div>


<div id="outline-container-org8ae29b2" class="outline-3">
<h3 id="org8ae29b2">Atomic Commands</h3>
<div class="outline-text-3" id="text-org8ae29b2">
<p>
A atomic command is one that can take multiple keys and values and do it in a all or fail manner
</p>

<p>
They operate the same except have a m added to the name
so <code>mset</code> would be <code>set</code>.
</p>

<p>
<code>del</code> can take multiple keys
</p>
